<p>I'm trying to login with an external provider. However, when I make a call to ExternalLogin it returns 302 Found. I understand why I get this error, but not sure how to solve it. What would be the best way to redirect browser to the external login site in my case?</p>  <p>Angular call</p>  <pre><code>$scope.log = function() {     var token = $("input[name='__RequestVerificationToken']").val();     return $http({         url: 'Account/ExternalLogin',         method: 'POST',         data: { "provider": "Google", "returnUrl": ""},         headers: {             '__RequestVerificationToken': token         }     }).success(function(data) {      }).error(function(err, status) {     }) } </code></pre>  <p>ExternalLogin</p>  <pre><code>[HttpPost] [AllowAnonymous] [ValidateJsonAntiForgeryToken] public ActionResult ExternalLogin(string provider, string returnUrl) {     // Request a redirect to the external login provider      return new ChallengeResult(provider, Url.Action("ExternalLoginCallback", "Account", new { ReturnUrl = returnUrl })); } </code></pre>